    <sectiondef kind="public-attrib">
      <memberdef kind="variable" id="structbt__gatt__attr_1a6958f507f9ff172018be458ebc86106f" prot="public" static="no" mutable="no">
        <type>const struct <ref refid="structbt__uuid" kindref="compound">bt_uuid</ref> *</type>
        <definition>const struct bt_uuid* bt_gatt_attr::uuid</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>uuid</name>
        <qualifiedname>bt_gatt_attr::uuid</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Attribute Type. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The Attribute Type is a UUID which determines the interface that can be expected from the <ref refid="structbt__gatt__attr_1a074abc719494ca35997a452f526e7ecc" kindref="member">read()</ref> and <ref refid="structbt__gatt__attr_1a1ecd78536067f4bded506e0daccefd35" kindref="member">write()</ref> methods and the possible permission configurations.</para>
<para>E.g. Attribute of type <ref refid="group__bt__uuid_1ga331a61702ffe9b15bac0de3d60414022" kindref="member">BT_UUID_GATT_CPF</ref> will act as a GATT Characteristic Presentation Format descriptor as specified in Core Specification 3.G.3.3.3.5.</para>
<para>You can define a new Attribute Type for your application specific use by generating a new UUID for it. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
