      <memberdef kind="variable" id="structbt__gatt__attr_1adeb063fb101fab45dd789c7212c43357" prot="public" static="no" mutable="no">
        <type>void *</type>
        <definition>void* bt_gatt_attr::user_data</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>user_data</name>
        <qualifiedname>bt_gatt_attr::user_data</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Private data for <ref refid="structbt__gatt__attr_1a074abc719494ca35997a452f526e7ecc" kindref="member">read()</ref> and <ref refid="structbt__gatt__attr_1a1ecd78536067f4bded506e0daccefd35" kindref="member">write()</ref> implementation. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The meaning of this field varies and is not specified here.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>Attributes may have the same Attribute Type but have different implementations, with incompatible user data. Attribute Type alone must not be used to infer the type of the user data.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="group__bt__gatt__client_1ga293c512555f2677f3c1b82c80f6fcfff" kindref="member">bt_gatt_discover_func_t</ref> about this field. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
